main event: A white egg-shaped object with a red tinge was observed on radar and visually for 15 to 25 minutes in DeFuniak Springs, Florida.
interesting points: The object was first seen at 10 degrees elevation and 135 degrees azimuth,The object's size kept flashing and going out of sight,The object was traveling west during the observation,The sighting included both ground-radar and civilian & military sources,There was a helicopter in the area that may have caused confusion regarding the sighting.
sighted object: one white egg-shaped object with a red tinge
